definition.value: An ommochrome that consists of a pyrido[3,2-a]phenoxazine ring system bearing hydroxy, carboxy, oxo and 3-amino-3-carboxypropanoyl substituents at positions 1, 3, 5 and 11 respectively. The parent of the class of xanthommatins.
A secondary alcohol that is nonane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.
A trehalose in which both glucose residues have alpha-configuration at the anomeric carbon.
A secondary alcohol that is heptane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
A L-methionine derivative in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a formyl group.
